1
00:00:40,373 --> 00:00:44,139
Three Communist PT boats
attacked an American destroyer

2
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:46,201
off the coast of Vietnam
yesterday,

3
00:00:46,279 --> 00:00:49,806
and today, President Johnson's
response was hard and tough.

4
00:00:51,284 --> 00:00:54,651
He has ordered the U.S. Navy
to continue patrolling there,

5
00:00:54,754 --> 00:00:58,019
and if they are attacked,
to destroy their attackers.

6
00:00:58,091 --> 00:01:00,116
I understand the feelings

7
00:01:00,226 --> 00:01:04,356
of those who regret that
we must undertake air attacks.

8
00:01:04,431 --> 00:01:06,194
I share those feelings.

9
00:01:06,266 --> 00:01:08,564
Some nights, we're
the only airplane going up...

10
00:01:08,635 --> 00:01:09,624
going up into the north

11
00:01:09,702 --> 00:01:11,897
and when you're thinking
you're the only Americans

12
00:01:11,971 --> 00:01:13,233
over North Vietnam,

13
00:01:13,306 --> 00:01:15,797
it kind of makes you wonder
just a little bit, you know.

14
00:01:15,875 --> 00:01:17,069
"What am I doing here?"

15
00:01:17,143 --> 00:01:20,203
We have carefully limited
those raids.

16
00:01:20,313 --> 00:01:23,214
They've been directed
at concrete and steel

17
00:01:23,283 --> 00:01:24,875
and not human lives.

18
00:01:24,984 --> 00:01:29,819
There are at least 850
antiaircraft and missile sites

19
00:01:29,889 --> 00:01:32,050
around Hanoi and Haiphong.

20
00:01:32,125 --> 00:01:34,855
These figures make
Hanoi's air defense

21
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:36,862
the toughest in the world.

22
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:38,295
If you can get between...

23
00:01:38,398 --> 00:01:40,229
a ridge between you
and that radar site,

24
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:41,858
they can't guide
a missile at you.

25
00:01:41,935 --> 00:01:44,631
It's just when you get down
in the delta in the flatlands,

26
00:01:44,704 --> 00:01:47,104
that 30-mile ring around...
the city of Hanoi,

27
00:01:47,173 --> 00:01:49,004
it's... it's a bear.

28
00:01:49,075 --> 00:01:52,943
Representatives of Hanoi
simply returned our message

29
00:01:53,012 --> 00:01:55,037
in a plain envelope.

30
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:58,050
Residents of North Vietnam's
capital felt confident

31
00:01:58,118 --> 00:02:00,484
in the knowledge
that their city was off-limits

32
00:02:00,553 --> 00:02:01,918
to U.S. warplanes.

33
00:02:01,988 --> 00:02:06,322
With American sons
in the fields far away,

34
00:02:06,392 --> 00:02:10,328
I shall not seek, and l
will not accept the nomination

35
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:13,831
of my party for another term
as your president.

36
00:02:13,933 --> 00:02:16,766
The greatest honor
history can bestow

37
00:02:16,836 --> 00:02:19,737
is the title of peacemaker.

38
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:21,000
Do you think it's worth it?

39
00:02:21,074 --> 00:02:22,439
Yeah, l... I don't know.

40
00:02:22,509 --> 00:02:24,568
They... they say we're
fighting for something.

41
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:25,611
I don't know.

42
00:02:25,678 --> 00:02:27,976
Through a long and bitter
struggle in Vietnam,

43
00:02:28,047 --> 00:02:29,139
American fighting men

44
00:02:29,215 --> 00:02:31,149
have served the cause
of freedom magnificently.

45
00:02:31,217 --> 00:02:32,878
You're... you're pretty scared

46
00:02:32,952 --> 00:02:35,182
when you have to roll in
on something out there,

47
00:02:35,255 --> 00:02:37,519
especially when you look down,
and you see nothing

48
00:02:37,624 --> 00:02:39,956
but a black cloud or
a white cloud down below you.

49
00:02:40,026 --> 00:02:43,052
It's a... it's about as...
as scary a mission

50
00:02:43,129 --> 00:02:44,528
as I've ever been on.

51
00:02:44,597 --> 00:02:48,055
I think it tries you
to just about the maximum,

52
00:02:48,134 --> 00:02:50,034
you know, the missions.

53
00:03:26,105 --> 00:03:28,164
Hey, Morg.

54
00:03:28,274 --> 00:03:29,764
Did you ever notice how...

55
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:31,935
how some nights you could see
more stars

56
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:34,445
than other nights?

57
00:03:34,514 --> 00:03:36,482
Huh? You ever notice that?

58
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:38,210
Hmm?

59
00:03:38,284 --> 00:03:39,979
The stars.

60
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:42,146
Oh, yeah.

61
00:03:43,423 --> 00:03:44,856
I've got an update.

62
00:03:44,924 --> 00:03:46,983
I'm cycling to
the coast-in point.

63
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,960
You're getting
in a rut.

64
00:03:49,028 --> 00:03:50,962
You're getting in a rut.

65
00:03:51,030 --> 00:03:52,429
I mean, did you ever
stop to think

66
00:03:52,498 --> 00:03:54,830
you're taking your job just
a little bit too seriously?

67
00:03:54,934 --> 00:03:56,128
Look at me--
I enjoy my work.

68
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:57,168
Yeah, I'll bet.

69
00:03:57,270 --> 00:03:58,237
See, I'm happy.

70
00:03:58,338 --> 00:03:59,327
See? Look.

71
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:04,767
Enemy search radar

72
00:04:04,844 --> 00:04:06,004
Iooking for company.

73
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:08,604
Okay...

74
00:04:08,681 --> 00:04:09,648
Time to get on down.

75
00:04:09,716 --> 00:04:10,740
Here we go.

76
00:04:24,297 --> 00:04:26,891
Black Eagle, Devil 5-0-5.
Feet dry.

77
00:04:26,966 --> 00:04:28,957
That's a roger, 5-0-5.

78
00:04:37,577 --> 00:04:39,511
Look at that small-arms fire
down there, Morg.

79
00:04:39,579 --> 00:04:42,070
Every cousin with a rifle, huh?

80
00:04:46,886 --> 00:04:49,184
Jesus, you call that a rifle?

81
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:51,688
I lost them.

82
00:04:51,758 --> 00:04:52,690
Yeah, you hope.

83
00:04:52,759 --> 00:04:53,521
You got that riverbend ahead?

84
00:04:53,593 --> 00:04:55,356
Just picked it up.

85
00:04:55,495 --> 00:04:57,554
One more minute on this heading
to the turn point.

86
00:04:59,265 --> 00:05:00,630
23 Mike, Mike-- I see them.

87
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,258
Go active on ECM.

88
00:05:02,335 --> 00:05:03,461
Jam 'em up.

89
00:05:03,536 --> 00:05:04,468
ECM active.

90
00:05:04,537 --> 00:05:05,595
We're jammin'.

91
00:05:13,413 --> 00:05:14,744
Where is it?
You got it? You see it?

92
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:15,838
No, not yet.

93
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:20,680
SAM, 10:00.

94
00:05:20,753 --> 00:05:21,515
Jam!

95
00:05:29,295 --> 00:05:31,024
Ah, Jesus.

96
00:05:31,097 --> 00:05:32,587
That was a piece of cake.

97
00:05:34,534 --> 00:05:35,728
This is it.

98
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:37,268
Stepping in to attack.

99
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:38,462
Arm 'em.

100
00:05:38,571 --> 00:05:39,560
Your pickle is hot.

101
00:05:39,672 --> 00:05:41,230
Get us up to 500 feet, partner,

102
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:42,740
unless you want to frag
your ass.

103
00:05:42,809 --> 00:05:44,674
Nag, nag, nag.

104
00:05:47,213 --> 00:05:48,475
Ground lock.

105
00:05:48,548 --> 00:05:49,276
Steady...

106
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:51,248
They're off!

107
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:00,492
If you got the time,

108
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,323
we got the beer.

109
00:06:06,232 --> 00:06:07,164
How about it?

110
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:08,165
Did you see anything down there?

111
00:06:08,234 --> 00:06:09,064
Any secondary explosions?

112
00:06:09,135 --> 00:06:10,159
Nothing.

113
00:06:10,236 --> 00:06:12,761
Well, that's real nice.

114
00:06:12,839 --> 00:06:14,033
-Suspected truck park.
-Nothing!

115
00:06:14,107 --> 00:06:15,039
Nothing.

116
00:06:15,108 --> 00:06:16,097
Goddamn it.

117
00:06:16,175 --> 00:06:18,040
Man, there was nothing there.

118
00:06:18,111 --> 00:06:19,100
There never was.

119
00:06:19,178 --> 00:06:21,112
Well, we're really raising hell

120
00:06:21,180 --> 00:06:23,410
with the jungle tonight,
aren't we?

121
00:06:28,755 --> 00:06:29,278
What is it?

122
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:30,413
What the hell is it?

123
00:06:30,523 --> 00:06:32,252
What is it?

124
00:06:32,325 --> 00:06:33,587
Oh, dear God.

125
00:06:35,161 --> 00:06:36,856
-Oh, God Almighty.
-You got to help me!

126
00:06:36,929 --> 00:06:38,055
Let go of it for a minute!

127
00:06:38,131 --> 00:06:39,063
I don't want to...

128
00:06:39,132 --> 00:06:40,861
Black Eagle,
this is Devil 5-0-5.

129
00:06:40,933 --> 00:06:42,525
I'm declaring emergency!

130
00:06:42,602 --> 00:06:44,536
My bombardier's been hit.

131
00:06:44,604 --> 00:06:46,265
I repeat:
my bombardier's been hit.

132
00:06:46,339 --> 00:06:48,102
Requesting a ready deck
upon arrival!

133
00:06:48,174 --> 00:06:50,108
I'll be on the bridge outside.

134
00:06:53,312 --> 00:06:55,246
This is the enforcer.
Make a ready deck.

135
00:06:55,348 --> 00:06:56,610
We have an emergency inbound.

136
00:06:56,682 --> 00:06:59,446
5-0-5, switch to button three
for approach.

137
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:01,050
Uh, roger that.

138
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,519
Button three, Devil 5-0-5.

139
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:04,215
Gear is down.

140
00:07:06,025 --> 00:07:07,515
I got to let go
just for a second.

141
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:08,582
Come on.
I can do it.

142
00:07:08,661 --> 00:07:10,356
-Got to hang on.
-I'm okay, Jakey.

143
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,954
Hang in there, shipmate.

144
00:07:12,031 --> 00:07:12,998
We're gonna make it.

145
00:07:13,065 --> 00:07:14,862
-Now keep the faith.
-I'll make it.

146
00:07:16,903 --> 00:07:19,337
No strain, partner.

147
00:07:20,606 --> 00:07:22,403
5-0-5, call your ball,
call your ball.

148
00:07:22,475 --> 00:07:24,033
200 ball, six point zero.

149
00:07:24,143 --> 00:07:25,075
Ride your ball.

150
00:07:25,144 --> 00:07:26,839
Working 22 knots.
You're high.

151
00:07:28,915 --> 00:07:29,939
We're gonna make it.

152
00:07:30,016 --> 00:07:31,074
Gotta hang in there.

153
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:32,708
Oh, geez.

154
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:34,116
Shit, he's still too high!

155
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,046
Jakey...

156
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:37,612
You're too high!

157
00:07:37,690 --> 00:07:38,952
Morg!

158
00:07:39,025 --> 00:07:40,686
Steady your line,
steady your line.

159
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:41,920
Come left, Jake.

160
00:07:43,496 --> 00:07:44,258
I'm coming in.

161
00:07:45,231 --> 00:07:46,698
He's too high!
Wave him off!

162
00:07:46,799 --> 00:07:49,233
5-0-5, wave off! Wave off!

163
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:01,571
Tie 'em down!
Tie 'em down!

164
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:03,239
I told you we'd make it, Morg.

165
00:08:03,382 --> 00:08:05,145
I told you we'd make it.

166
00:08:05,218 --> 00:08:06,685
Everything's cool...

167
00:08:06,752 --> 00:08:07,241
We made it, Morg.

168
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,014
I told you we'd make it.

169
00:08:08,087 --> 00:08:09,349
I got him, sir, I got him.

170
00:08:09,422 --> 00:08:10,719
Just let go, for Christ's sake.

171
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:11,255
Let go!

172
00:08:11,424 --> 00:08:12,049
Let go of him, sir!

173
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:12,624
I got him!

174
00:08:12,725 --> 00:08:14,158
Come on, goddamn it!

175
00:08:14,227 --> 00:08:15,660
Let go of him,
for Christ's sake!

176
00:08:15,728 --> 00:08:16,786
Let me out,
corpsman, come on!

177
00:08:16,863 --> 00:08:18,558
I need some pressure in here!

178
00:08:18,631 --> 00:08:19,996
Get him out of here, goddamn it!

179
00:08:20,066 --> 00:08:20,862
Medic, come on!

180
00:08:20,933 --> 00:08:22,161
Watch, watch the head.

181
00:08:22,235 --> 00:08:23,259
Stand by!

182
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:25,736
Bring it in, bring it in,
bring it in! Move it!

183
00:08:25,805 --> 00:08:27,568
Morg!

184
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:29,301
He's gone, man.

185
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:30,637
Come on, Jake.

186
00:08:30,710 --> 00:08:31,802
Come on.

187
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:36,175
Oh, Jesus Christ, man.

188
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:38,647
It'll be all right, Jake.

189
00:08:38,718 --> 00:08:40,481
It's going to be all right, man.

190
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:04,942
Jake, we don't want any more
of this if we can help it.

191
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:08,013
What altitude were you at
when McPherson got hit?

192
00:09:08,114 --> 00:09:10,173
300, 500...
something like that.

193
00:09:10,249 --> 00:09:13,013
I'd just taken a gun out
with a snake eye.

194
00:09:13,085 --> 00:09:14,017
300 or 500?

195
00:09:14,086 --> 00:09:15,348
It makes a difference.

196
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:17,287
I don't know.

197
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:18,448
I'm a little shaken up
right now.

198
00:09:18,524 --> 00:09:19,513
You're what?

199
00:09:19,592 --> 00:09:21,287
I said I'm shaken up, sir.

200
00:09:21,427 --> 00:09:23,520
I got Morg's blood all over me.

201
00:09:23,596 --> 00:09:25,223
Maybe we can stop the war

202
00:09:25,298 --> 00:09:26,697
till things get better then.

203
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:29,393
Nobody asked you to stop
the war, did they?

204
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:34,165
Put McPherson's death
behind you, Mr. Grafton.

205
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:37,869
Right here, right now.

206
00:09:37,944 --> 00:09:40,879
Yes, sir.

207
00:09:42,315 --> 00:09:45,216
Now, what altitude
were you flying at?

208
00:09:47,153 --> 00:09:49,246
Uh... 200.

209
00:09:49,322 --> 00:09:52,519
200 maybe, AGL.

210
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:54,684
I pushed the nose over...

211
00:09:54,794 --> 00:09:55,886
started a shallow...

212
00:09:55,995 --> 00:09:59,021
dive in on the gun
and leveled out.

213
00:09:59,131 --> 00:10:01,793
Some SAMs had tried us
when we'd come in,

214
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:05,234
and I wanted to... to get
out of there low and fast.

215
00:10:05,304 --> 00:10:06,828
You came out
by a different route?

216
00:10:08,574 --> 00:10:09,632
Yeah. Yes, sir.

217
00:10:09,709 --> 00:10:11,108
About 30 miles, I guess.

218
00:10:11,177 --> 00:10:12,610
Lucky small-arms fire.

219
00:10:12,678 --> 00:10:13,610
Mmm.

220
00:10:13,679 --> 00:10:14,611
All right.

221
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:16,307
Just bad luck, that's all.

222
00:10:16,382 --> 00:10:18,646
Just ran out of luck.

223
00:10:18,751 --> 00:10:21,686
Take Mr. Grafton
off the flight schedule.

224
00:10:21,754 --> 00:10:25,747
You got liberty in Subic
in a couple days.

225
00:10:25,825 --> 00:10:27,816
You need the rest.

226
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:30,057
What was your target?

227
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:33,458
A suspected truck park.

228
00:10:33,566 --> 00:10:34,464
You hit it?

229
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,567
Oh, yeah, we hit it.

230
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:36,567
Trees.

231
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:37,796
A bunch of trees.

232
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:40,031
There was nothing there again.

233
00:10:40,106 --> 00:10:41,038
What's your problem?

234
00:10:41,107 --> 00:10:43,701
Spit it out.

235
00:10:46,579 --> 00:10:49,514
Well, I don't think trees
in a suspected truck park

236
00:10:49,615 --> 00:10:50,912
is worth a man's life.

237
00:10:52,718 --> 00:10:55,016
Targets are picked for
political consideration,

238
00:10:55,087 --> 00:10:56,247
Mr. Grafton,

239
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:58,085
with the best intelligence
we have available.

240
00:10:58,157 --> 00:10:59,681
You have any trouble with that?

241
00:10:59,759 --> 00:11:01,351
Well, I don't think losing Morg

242
00:11:01,427 --> 00:11:03,327
is a political
consideration, sir.

243
00:11:06,032 --> 00:11:07,863
Look...

244
00:11:07,933 --> 00:11:10,902
I know losing
McPherson is lousy.

245
00:11:11,003 --> 00:11:12,937
I don't like the targets,
either.

246
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:14,063
I hate them.

247
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:17,438
But... I don't want any
blood feuds going on.

248
00:11:17,543 --> 00:11:19,306
Half the time,
it isn't the mission

249
00:11:19,378 --> 00:11:20,436
you're flying
that kills you,

250
00:11:20,579 --> 00:11:22,103
it's the one before--
do you read me?

251
00:11:24,316 --> 00:11:25,647
Yes, sir.

252
00:11:25,718 --> 00:11:27,083
Good.

253
00:11:27,153 --> 00:11:29,587
I want you to write
a letter to Morg's wife.

254
00:11:29,655 --> 00:11:31,418
I'll mail it in
a couple of days

255
00:11:31,490 --> 00:11:32,787
along with one from me.

256
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:35,224
Help put this thing
behind you, okay?

257
00:11:38,097 --> 00:11:39,394
Thanks, skipper.

258
00:11:39,465 --> 00:11:40,830
For what?

259
00:11:41,901 --> 00:11:44,768
You die, son, and
I'll piss on your grave.

260
00:11:58,818 --> 00:12:00,979
Down here, down here.

261
00:12:01,487 --> 00:12:02,317
Hey, Jake. Jake!

262
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:03,377
What the hell?

263
00:12:03,456 --> 00:12:05,287
You're not thinking
about jumping are you?

264
00:12:05,357 --> 00:12:06,324
No, not yet.

265
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:07,154
You need any help,
Mr. Grafton?

266
00:12:07,259 --> 00:12:08,521
We thought you might want
to talk or something.

267
00:12:08,627 --> 00:12:09,787
Oh, I'm fine.
Thanks, Chief.

268
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:11,089
So Jake, how'd you guys do?

269
00:12:11,197 --> 00:12:12,994
I mean, you know,
before it happened.

270
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:13,997
Trees.

271
00:12:14,066 --> 00:12:14,998
Yeah, trees?

272
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:15,999
Right.

273
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:17,092
-Again.
-Again?

274
00:12:17,203 --> 00:12:19,569
Hey, Jack, you were
with a Marine detachment.

275
00:12:19,638 --> 00:12:21,105
You ever
get used to it?

276
00:12:21,173 --> 00:12:22,333
Yeah, I got used to it.

277
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:23,898
I'm a doc-- that's what I do.

278
00:12:23,976 --> 00:12:25,102
Naw, nobody gets used to it.

279
00:12:25,177 --> 00:12:27,338
You can put your job in front
of it like the skipper,

280
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:29,847
or you can even joke about it,
but nobody gets used to it.

281
00:12:29,915 --> 00:12:30,643
That's right.

282
00:12:30,716 --> 00:12:32,013
How about the old man?

283
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:34,109
Has he always been
like he is now?

284
00:12:34,220 --> 00:12:35,653
When he chews you out?

285
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:36,847
Mm-hmm.

286
00:12:36,956 --> 00:12:39,754
Maybe he figures he might not
get another chance.

287
00:12:39,825 --> 00:12:40,917
Hey, guys, come on.

288
00:12:40,993 --> 00:12:42,824
We got a squad room meeting,
okay, Jake?

289
00:12:42,895 --> 00:12:44,726
All right, all right, all right.

290
00:12:44,797 --> 00:12:46,059
I got all night, too.

291
00:12:47,666 --> 00:12:50,635
I want to introduce
our new replacement pilot.

292
00:12:50,703 --> 00:12:52,068
Mr. Barlow, up front.

293
00:12:52,138 --> 00:12:54,732
Let's hear about your life.
Come on.

294
00:12:54,807 --> 00:12:56,274
Yeah! Yeah!

295
00:12:56,342 --> 00:12:58,810
Up front, up front,
up front, up front,

296
00:12:58,878 --> 00:13:00,106
up front, up front,
up front...

297
00:13:00,212 --> 00:13:01,144
All right.

298
00:13:01,213 --> 00:13:02,475
All right, all right, shut up!

299
00:13:02,548 --> 00:13:04,948
I'm Lieutenant J.G. Jack Barlow.

300
00:13:05,017 --> 00:13:06,678
Sit down, asshole!

301
00:13:06,752 --> 00:13:07,946
How old are you, son?

302
00:13:09,054 --> 00:13:09,986
24, sir.

303
00:13:10,055 --> 00:13:11,079
You look 12.

304
00:13:11,223 --> 00:13:13,589
Did they teach you how to shave
at the Naval Academy?

305
00:13:13,659 --> 00:13:14,455
I didn't think so.

306
00:13:14,527 --> 00:13:16,051
Razor.

307
00:13:16,128 --> 00:13:19,564
Ah, that's your new
name for now: Razor.

308
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:20,656
Excellent name, skipper.

309
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:21,665
Yeah!

310
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:23,031
All right, Walter.

311
00:13:23,102 --> 00:13:24,296
Thank you.

312
00:13:26,272 --> 00:13:27,296
All right, at, uh...

313
00:13:27,406 --> 00:13:29,271
tomorrow at 1000
on the flight deck

314
00:13:29,341 --> 00:13:31,901
there will be a memorial service
for McPherson.

315
00:13:31,977 --> 00:13:34,810
The uniform is tropical,
white, long.

316
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:36,905
Oh, yeah, one other thing.

317
00:13:36,982 --> 00:13:39,416
Uh, somebody close that door
back there, will you?

318
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:40,782
Frank?

319
00:13:42,688 --> 00:13:45,748
Now, this matter
of the phantom shitter.

320
00:13:47,226 --> 00:13:49,091
Now, I know it's a phenomenon

321
00:13:49,195 --> 00:13:51,322
that occurs on a
carrier in combat

322
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:53,421
that goes back
to World War I l,

323
00:13:53,532 --> 00:13:55,659
but this has gotten
out of hand.

324
00:13:55,734 --> 00:13:58,066
Last night, the
phantom left a note

325
00:13:58,137 --> 00:13:59,661
saying he would strike,

326
00:13:59,738 --> 00:14:03,504
and this morning, a turd was
found in the XO's ashtray.

327
00:14:05,744 --> 00:14:08,770
That only means
one thing, gentlemen.

328
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:11,214
It is no fighter jock
or recon puke

329
00:14:11,283 --> 00:14:12,875
who is doing this thing.

330
00:14:12,952 --> 00:14:14,317
It is an A-6 driver,

331
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:16,547
because no one else
on this ship

332
00:14:16,655 --> 00:14:18,486
can hit the XO's ashtray.

333
00:14:18,557 --> 00:14:19,581
Yeah!

334
00:14:21,327 --> 00:14:22,624
Right, right, right.

335
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:23,627
Hup.

336
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,891
Someone,

337
00:14:25,965 --> 00:14:30,265
in this room right here,

338
00:14:30,336 --> 00:14:32,327
is the phantom shitter.

339
00:14:32,404 --> 00:14:36,067
Now, it could be your roommate,
pilot, bombardier...

340
00:14:36,141 --> 00:14:38,336
Think about it.

341
00:14:38,410 --> 00:14:39,536
Movie officer.

342
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:40,544
Yes, sir.

343
00:14:40,646 --> 00:14:42,273
What's the film for tonight?

344
00:14:42,381 --> 00:14:44,508
Uh, They Shoot Horses,
Don't They?, sir.

345
00:14:44,617 --> 00:14:45,709
It's Jane Fonda, sir.

346
00:14:45,818 --> 00:14:46,716
Any skin?

347
00:14:46,785 --> 00:14:47,717
No, sir.

348
00:14:47,786 --> 00:14:48,684
Cancel it.

349
00:14:48,754 --> 00:14:50,085
Yeah!

350
00:14:56,395 --> 00:14:58,158
Dear Sharon,

351
00:14:58,230 --> 00:15:01,063
By now you've been notified
that Morgan is gone.

352
00:15:01,133 --> 00:15:03,863
He was killed over Vietnam
flying a night strike

353
00:15:03,936 --> 00:15:07,497
and... I wish I could say
that his death was necessary,

354
00:15:07,606 --> 00:15:10,131
but... it wasn't.

355
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:13,511
The target we were bombing
was nonexistent,

356
00:15:13,579 --> 00:15:16,844
and the mission was useless.

357
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:21,216
Too many good men have died like
Morgan these past two years.

358
00:15:21,287 --> 00:15:24,814
I guess I knew him as well
as any man could know another.

359
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:28,291
He was... he was my best friend.

360
00:15:29,795 --> 00:15:31,353
I know how heavy a burden

361
00:15:31,463 --> 00:15:33,658
his loss is to you
and little Bobby,

362
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:36,291
and... and I know
how much he loved you.

363
00:15:36,402 --> 00:15:39,064
Somehow I wish
there was something,

364
00:15:39,138 --> 00:15:40,571
just one thing I could do

365
00:15:40,639 --> 00:15:43,665
to make up for such a loss
as Morgan.

366
00:15:43,742 --> 00:15:45,710
I go on, as Tennyson said,

367
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:48,406
and the world darkens around me,

368
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:53,179
"among new men, strange faces"
and other minds.

369
00:15:53,319 --> 00:15:56,152
You have my deepest
and most sincere sympathy.

370
00:15:56,221 --> 00:15:57,313
Jake.

371
00:16:32,758 --> 00:16:35,090
Real sorry about Mr. McPherson,
sir.

372
00:16:36,795 --> 00:16:37,989
What's this?

373
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:44,093
Thought he was single.

374
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:45,397
He was.

375
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:47,336
He was four days ago.

376
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:50,031
You know this girl, Chief?

377
00:16:50,142 --> 00:16:51,973
Yeah, she's a looker.

378
00:16:52,044 --> 00:16:56,071
Probably first piece of ass
he's ever had.

379
00:16:56,148 --> 00:16:58,013
When did you get married, son?

380
00:16:58,083 --> 00:17:00,551
Last time in port, sir.

381
00:17:00,619 --> 00:17:02,280
You know you got to have
Navy permission

382
00:17:02,354 --> 00:17:04,515
to marry a foreign national?

383
00:17:04,590 --> 00:17:06,285
Your folks know?

384
00:17:06,358 --> 00:17:08,690
No, sir.

385
00:17:08,761 --> 00:17:10,524
Do you love her?

386
00:17:10,596 --> 00:17:13,190
Well, yes, sir,
of course I do, sir.

387
00:17:13,265 --> 00:17:15,233
I-I got a picture of
her here in my wallet.

388
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:16,824
No, that's all right.
It's all right.

389
00:17:18,203 --> 00:17:20,797
You violated a major
regulation, Hardesty,

390
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:22,864
but I'm going to sign
your chit.

391
00:17:24,176 --> 00:17:25,700
You realize that you're legally

392
00:17:25,778 --> 00:17:27,541
and morally obligated
to this girl.

393
00:17:27,613 --> 00:17:28,739
Do you know that?

394
00:17:28,814 --> 00:17:30,111
Yes, sir.

395
00:17:30,182 --> 00:17:31,706
Do you understand
what that means?

396
00:17:31,784 --> 00:17:32,842
You got to support her.

397
00:17:32,918 --> 00:17:33,976
Yes, sir.

398
00:17:43,262 --> 00:17:45,253
This aircraft
has not been cleaned!

399
00:17:45,364 --> 00:17:46,956
Why hasn't this aircraft
been cleaned?

400
00:17:47,032 --> 00:17:48,499
I'll clean it myself, sir.

401
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:49,966
I'll see that it's done.

402
00:17:50,035 --> 00:17:52,026
You do that,
you get it done!

403
00:17:52,104 --> 00:17:53,071
Get it clean!

404
00:17:57,810 --> 00:17:58,902
Sorry, sir, l...

405
00:17:58,977 --> 00:18:01,343
No, don't explain, son,
just get it done.

406
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:03,074
Mr. Grafton won't hold it
against you.

407
00:18:03,215 --> 00:18:04,648
He's just upset.

408
00:18:04,716 --> 00:18:06,183
It's just that nobody's ever

409
00:18:06,285 --> 00:18:07,877
come back dead like that, sir.

410
00:18:07,986 --> 00:18:08,975
Whole ship knows about it.

411
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:10,020
A lot of them come down

412
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:11,420
just to take a look
at it, but...

413
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:13,117
I don't know why we
didn't clean it, sir.

414
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:14,691
When people die,
they're just gone.

415
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:15,522
But not like this, sir.

416
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:16,561
All right, all right.

417
00:18:16,628 --> 00:18:18,289
That's all right, son,
that's all right.

418
00:18:29,675 --> 00:18:31,006
This is the enforcer.

419
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:32,509
Stand by to recover the call.

420
00:18:49,194 --> 00:18:51,128
Mr. Cole!
How you doing?

421
00:18:51,196 --> 00:18:53,130
I'm Chief Poole.
You come this way.

422
00:18:53,232 --> 00:18:54,824
Commander Camparelli
is waiting for you

423
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:55,832
down in the ready room.

424
00:18:55,901 --> 00:18:56,833
Hold on, Chief.

425
00:18:56,902 --> 00:18:57,869
All right, sir.

426
00:19:00,973 --> 00:19:02,565
I want to smell it.

427
00:19:04,610 --> 00:19:06,271
I've been away for a while.

428
00:19:09,615 --> 00:19:10,547
I'm ready.

429
00:19:10,616 --> 00:19:11,583
All right, sir.

430
00:19:16,622 --> 00:19:17,782
Mr. Cole.

431
00:19:19,124 --> 00:19:20,216
Have a seat.

432
00:19:20,292 --> 00:19:21,759
I'm fine, sir.

433
00:19:29,568 --> 00:19:30,899
Uh...

434
00:19:32,271 --> 00:19:35,707
I was on the Coral Sea,
when you were on the Ranger.

435
00:19:35,774 --> 00:19:36,934
Is that so?

436
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:40,274
Knew a lot of guys
in VA-35.

437
00:19:40,379 --> 00:19:42,813
Knew Jim Becker.

438
00:19:42,948 --> 00:19:44,210
Flew A-4s with him.

439
00:19:44,283 --> 00:19:45,716
You went down with him,
didn't you?

440
00:19:45,784 --> 00:19:47,684
That's right, sir.

441
00:19:48,921 --> 00:19:51,048
And he didn't make it.

442
00:19:51,123 --> 00:19:52,750
No, sir, he didn't.

443
00:19:57,095 --> 00:19:59,825
I know the whole story.

444
00:19:59,898 --> 00:20:01,957
Before and after.

445
00:20:03,535 --> 00:20:05,025
I know a lot about you.

446
00:20:05,137 --> 00:20:06,627
Well, I'm glad, sir,

447
00:20:06,738 --> 00:20:09,536
because I know a lot
about you, too.

448
00:20:09,608 --> 00:20:12,042
Everybody in the Navy
knows about you, sir.

449
00:20:12,144 --> 00:20:13,543
Yeah?

450
00:20:13,612 --> 00:20:14,772
What about me?

451
00:20:16,515 --> 00:20:18,346
That you're a legend, sir.

452
00:20:18,417 --> 00:20:20,510
Then that makes two of us.

453
00:20:20,586 --> 00:20:23,453
And sometimes that can
be a bad influence on others.

454
00:20:23,522 --> 00:20:26,514
I'll try and fit in, sir.

455
00:20:26,592 --> 00:20:28,184
That's my job.

456
00:20:28,260 --> 00:20:30,194
Make sure you do that.

457
00:20:30,295 --> 00:20:32,195
Good evening, Mr. Cole.

458
00:20:33,899 --> 00:20:36,891
We'll have to try
Sector A tomorrow.

459
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:37,933
Finding out now...

460
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:39,037
Mr. Grafton.

461
00:20:39,104 --> 00:20:41,595
I'm sorry about
Mr. McPherson, sir.

462
00:20:42,941 --> 00:20:43,873
Is, uh, Guffy around?

463
00:20:43,942 --> 00:20:44,874
You seen him?

464
00:20:44,943 --> 00:20:45,875
Uh, yes, sir.

465
00:20:45,944 --> 00:20:47,275
He's... he's right there.

466
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:53,384
You wanted to see me, Guffy?

467
00:20:53,452 --> 00:20:54,578
Yeah, just a minute.

468
00:21:00,792 --> 00:21:02,157
Let me ask you something, Guffy.

469
00:21:02,227 --> 00:21:06,493
You suppose there's anything...
anything valuable here?

470
00:21:06,565 --> 00:21:09,762
If they had something,
it'd be up north, wouldn't it?

471
00:21:09,835 --> 00:21:12,235
That's right, Mr. Grafton.

472
00:21:12,304 --> 00:21:13,794
You see this?

473
00:21:13,872 --> 00:21:15,430
This is Haiphong Harbor.

474
00:21:15,507 --> 00:21:17,668
It's loaded with munitions.

475
00:21:17,743 --> 00:21:20,075
They take 'em out of here,

476
00:21:20,145 --> 00:21:21,976
and they stick 'em here,
in Hanoi.

477
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:24,344
But it's not for you,
it's restricted.

478
00:21:24,416 --> 00:21:25,849
They didn't do it in '65,

479
00:21:25,951 --> 00:21:28,010
we haven't flown
over it since '69,

480
00:21:28,086 --> 00:21:29,815
so don't even think about it.

481
00:21:29,888 --> 00:21:31,321
But I do have something here

482
00:21:31,390 --> 00:21:32,914
that's gonna
brighten your day.

483
00:21:33,025 --> 00:21:35,493
You know that strike you flew in
the south last week?

484
00:21:36,528 --> 00:21:38,257
Yeah, we refueled at Da Nang.

485
00:21:38,330 --> 00:21:39,262
That one?

486
00:21:39,331 --> 00:21:40,389
Yeah.

487
00:21:40,465 --> 00:21:42,831
Army bomb damage assessment
says you killed 37.

488
00:21:42,901 --> 00:21:44,630
That's some body count,
eh, buddy?

489
00:21:47,239 --> 00:21:48,706
You think I want
to know that, huh?

490
00:21:48,807 --> 00:21:51,241
If you did what I did,
would you want to know?

491
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:53,301
No, for all you know,
those people were farmers.

492
00:21:53,412 --> 00:21:54,436
You get that information,

493
00:21:54,513 --> 00:21:55,980
you keep it to yourself,
all right?

494
00:21:56,048 --> 00:21:57,276
I don't want to know about it.

495
00:21:57,349 --> 00:21:58,441
Just keep it to yourself.

496
00:22:02,254 --> 00:22:04,415
Do you even know who I am?

497
00:22:04,489 --> 00:22:05,615
Yes, sir, I do, sir!

498
00:22:05,691 --> 00:22:08,057
You're Commander Camparelli,
sir, the C.O.!

499
00:22:08,126 --> 00:22:09,957
What kind of name
is Camparelli?!

500
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:13,855
It is an ltalian-
American name.

501
00:22:13,965 --> 00:22:16,490
Have you ever met a black man
with a name like that?

502
00:22:16,601 --> 00:22:18,728
No, you haven't.

503
00:22:18,804 --> 00:22:20,135
I got that name

504
00:22:20,205 --> 00:22:22,366
because somewhere in my past
there was a wop

505
00:22:22,441 --> 00:22:23,999
in the woodpile.

506
00:22:24,076 --> 00:22:26,237
Do I detect a smile

507
00:22:26,311 --> 00:22:29,337
on your disgusting face,
Lieutenant Razor?

508
00:22:29,414 --> 00:22:31,712
I thought not.

509
00:22:31,783 --> 00:22:36,584
So it turns out that my family
are third-generation Mafia.

510
00:22:36,655 --> 00:22:38,350
They were forced to make
a living in gambling,

511
00:22:38,457 --> 00:22:41,893
extortion and murder,
so that their boy

512
00:22:41,993 --> 00:22:44,655
could fly a jet aircraft
for the U.S. Navy.

513
00:22:44,730 --> 00:22:46,493
So I take what I do serious.

514
00:22:46,565 --> 00:22:48,192
Do you understand me, son?

515
00:22:48,266 --> 00:22:50,234
Yes, sir, I do, sir.

516
00:22:50,302 --> 00:22:51,735
Then get out of my sight.

517
00:22:51,803 --> 00:22:54,772
Lieutenant Razor, dismissed!

518
00:22:59,177 --> 00:23:00,906
Ah-- don't laugh.

519
00:23:00,979 --> 00:23:02,412
He's your new wingman.

520
00:23:05,517 --> 00:23:06,449
Just take one.

521
00:23:06,518 --> 00:23:07,917
I'll hand it to you.

522
00:23:09,187 --> 00:23:10,916
That's the one
I want you to have.

523
00:23:13,558 --> 00:23:18,086
There's a pair of A-6s
going to Subic tomorrow.

524
00:23:18,163 --> 00:23:20,688
I want you take one
with the doc.

525
00:23:20,766 --> 00:23:24,532
I'll put Grafton and maybe
Boxman in the other one.

526
00:23:24,603 --> 00:23:26,901
As soon as you get
Jake off the deck,

527
00:23:26,972 --> 00:23:29,031
you fly him dizzy,
get him drunk,

528
00:23:29,107 --> 00:23:32,372
anything to wind him down
before he goes up in flames.

529
00:23:32,477 --> 00:23:33,409
Yeah...

530
00:23:35,847 --> 00:23:39,510
All that guy needs is a...

531
00:23:39,584 --> 00:23:40,949
strike on the match.

532
00:23:43,221 --> 00:23:44,313
All right, now listen, Doc.

533
00:23:44,389 --> 00:23:45,321
Don't touch anything.

534
00:23:45,390 --> 00:23:46,357
