1072
00:53:39,783 --> 00:53:41,683
Let's go home.

1073
00:53:52,696 --> 00:53:55,529
Wash the windows,
check the oil.

1074
00:53:55,632 --> 00:53:57,122
Hey, what happened
to you guys?

1075
00:53:57,234 --> 00:54:00,032
A couple of minutes back there
you didn't answer my calls.

1076
00:54:00,103 --> 00:54:01,070
Oh, that.

1077
00:54:01,171 --> 00:54:02,661
We had a MiG after us.

1078
00:54:02,772 --> 00:54:05,332
We did an engine shutdown
to throw him off.

1079
00:54:05,408 --> 00:54:07,672
In the middle of combat?

1080
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:09,609
Whew.

1081
00:54:10,213 --> 00:54:11,578
Cool move.

1082
00:54:11,648 --> 00:54:12,979
Cool as a jewel.

1083
00:54:15,752 --> 00:54:17,447
That's bullshit.

1084
00:54:17,520 --> 00:54:19,147
I pulled back on the throttles
too much.

1085
00:54:19,222 --> 00:54:20,985
That was a major screw-up,
and you know it.

1086
00:54:21,057 --> 00:54:22,524
Well, don't worry.

1087
00:54:22,626 --> 00:54:24,856
It won't affect my decision.

1088
00:54:24,928 --> 00:54:26,418
Your what?

1089
00:54:26,529 --> 00:54:29,862
If you were a candy ass,
I'd ask for a new pilot,

1090
00:54:29,933 --> 00:54:31,298
but I figure you'll do.

1091
00:54:41,711 --> 00:54:43,076
Hey, Jake.

1092
00:54:43,146 --> 00:54:44,113
Hey, man.

1093
00:54:44,180 --> 00:54:45,112
Hey.

1094
00:54:45,181 --> 00:54:46,910
What you doing up here?

1095
00:54:46,983 --> 00:54:48,848
Ah, it's a good place to think.

1096
00:54:48,918 --> 00:54:49,816
Oh, yeah?

1097
00:54:49,886 --> 00:54:50,614
Me, too, huh.

1098
00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:52,449
I like the noise.

1099
00:54:52,555 --> 00:54:53,544
It's good, it's good.

1100
00:54:53,657 --> 00:54:55,557
What do you got there, Box?

1101
00:54:55,625 --> 00:54:56,751
Um...

1102
00:54:56,826 --> 00:54:59,818
It's just some mail,
you know, outgoing.

1103
00:54:59,896 --> 00:55:01,193
Is that all yours?

1104
00:55:01,264 --> 00:55:02,322
Well, yeah.

1105
00:55:02,399 --> 00:55:04,264
I got a lot of people
to write to, man.

1106
00:55:04,334 --> 00:55:06,325
This is only Post City,
actually.

1107
00:55:06,403 --> 00:55:07,802
These are my favorites.

1108
00:55:07,871 --> 00:55:08,997
These I like, too.

1109
00:55:09,072 --> 00:55:10,300
Now, wait a minute.

1110
00:55:10,373 --> 00:55:12,534
You had time for this
and for evaluation?

1111
00:55:12,676 --> 00:55:15,167
I got a lot
of responsibilities, man,

1112
00:55:15,245 --> 00:55:16,337
you know?

1113
00:55:16,446 --> 00:55:18,505
I'm a...

1114
00:55:18,615 --> 00:55:19,741
I'm a patriarch.

1115
00:55:21,051 --> 00:55:21,983
No, really.

1116
00:55:22,052 --> 00:55:22,984
A patriarch.

1117
00:55:23,053 --> 00:55:24,020
Yeah.

1118
00:55:24,120 --> 00:55:25,678
Want to hear something?

1119
00:55:25,755 --> 00:55:27,017
What do you got?

1120
00:55:27,090 --> 00:55:28,557
Hold on.

1121
00:55:32,262 --> 00:55:33,524
Wait till you hear this.

1122
00:55:33,596 --> 00:55:34,688
It's something else.

1123
00:55:34,764 --> 00:55:35,856
Listen to this.

1124
00:55:35,932 --> 00:55:36,921
Ready?

1125
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:39,696
Yeah.

1126
00:55:45,608 --> 00:55:47,041
You hear that?

1127
00:55:47,143 --> 00:55:48,474
"Daddy."

1128
00:55:48,545 --> 00:55:49,637
No, no, no.

1129
00:55:49,713 --> 00:55:52,807
He said "daddy," man.
That's my son.

1130
00:55:52,882 --> 00:55:54,747
That's my son.
It's beautiful, huh?

1131
00:55:54,818 --> 00:55:56,285
That's your son?

1132
00:55:56,353 --> 00:55:57,752
How'd you know?

1133
00:55:57,821 --> 00:55:59,948
I don't know, and I don't
give a shit either.

1134
00:56:01,157 --> 00:56:03,022
He can be my son
if he wants to be.

1135
00:56:03,093 --> 00:56:04,185
Why not?
Sure he can. Yes.

1136
00:56:04,260 --> 00:56:05,693
Right? I mean,
she wants him to be.

1137
00:56:05,762 --> 00:56:06,854
So do l.

1138
00:56:06,930 --> 00:56:08,522
I mean, that's what's
important, right?

1139
00:56:08,631 --> 00:56:10,189
That's right,
that's what's important.

1140
00:56:10,300 --> 00:56:11,858
Right. Right.

1141
00:56:11,968 --> 00:56:13,060
What's she like?

1142
00:56:13,169 --> 00:56:14,796
She's butt ugly.

1143
00:56:14,871 --> 00:56:15,860
I mean, she's ugly,

1144
00:56:15,939 --> 00:56:17,668
but she's got a great body, man.

1145
00:56:17,741 --> 00:56:19,368
Well, you know...

1146
00:56:19,442 --> 00:56:20,374
You know, Jake,

1147
00:56:20,443 --> 00:56:21,967
I think I could love
an ugly woman.

1148
00:56:22,045 --> 00:56:23,444
I mean, you can trust her more.

1149
00:56:23,513 --> 00:56:24,445
The pretty ones...

1150
00:56:24,514 --> 00:56:26,038
they only care about
themselves, right?

1151
00:56:26,116 --> 00:56:27,174
Yeah.

1152
00:56:27,250 --> 00:56:28,182
Right? I mean,
you know what I mean.

1153
00:56:28,251 --> 00:56:29,183
Yeah, sure.

1154
00:56:29,252 --> 00:56:31,152
That's nice.

1155
00:56:32,655 --> 00:56:33,349
Yeah?

1156
00:56:33,456 --> 00:56:34,445
Yeah.

1157
00:56:34,557 --> 00:56:36,252
Thanks a lot, Jake.

1158
00:56:36,359 --> 00:56:38,293
Yeah. Thanks a lot, man.

1159
00:56:38,361 --> 00:56:39,293
All right.

1160
00:56:39,362 --> 00:56:40,386
I'll see you around.

1161
00:56:40,497 --> 00:56:42,260
All right.

1162
00:56:57,147 --> 00:56:58,375
Mr. Grafton.

1163
00:57:04,721 --> 00:57:06,211
You wouldn't happen
to have anything

1164
00:57:06,322 --> 00:57:07,380
on North Vietnam, would you?

1165
00:57:07,457 --> 00:57:08,822
Like what?

1166
00:57:08,892 --> 00:57:10,792
Oh, I don't know.

1167
00:57:10,860 --> 00:57:14,125
Anything with...
maybe some maps?

1168
00:57:18,101 --> 00:57:19,568
Try this Geographic.

1169
00:57:19,702 --> 00:57:21,363
The map's in the back.

1170
00:57:21,438 --> 00:57:22,370
Keep it quiet.

1171
00:57:22,439 --> 00:57:24,805
It's not supposed to circulate.

1172
00:57:24,874 --> 00:57:27,240
All right. Thanks.

1173
00:57:39,389 --> 00:57:41,653
You want to bomb Hanoi.

1174
00:57:44,694 --> 00:57:46,958
You realize I could have you
court-martialed

1175
00:57:47,030 --> 00:57:48,691
for even making the suggestion.

1176
00:57:48,765 --> 00:57:50,096
That's right.

1177
00:57:50,166 --> 00:57:51,565
You took a big risk.

1178
00:57:51,668 --> 00:57:52,396
Yes, I did.

1179
00:57:55,772 --> 00:57:57,000
Why do you want to do this?

1180
00:57:57,073 --> 00:57:58,938
I think you know why.

1181
00:57:59,008 --> 00:58:02,444
There's guys like Morgan...

1182
00:58:02,512 --> 00:58:07,245
they're dying every day,
every single day.

1183
00:58:07,317 --> 00:58:08,306
This war...

1184
00:58:08,418 --> 00:58:10,545
This war's not going to end.

1185
00:58:10,653 --> 00:58:12,018
You think it would matter?

1186
00:58:12,088 --> 00:58:13,282
One plane?

1187
00:58:13,356 --> 00:58:14,584
Yes, I do.

1188
00:58:14,657 --> 00:58:15,817
It would matter to me.

1189
00:58:15,892 --> 00:58:17,484
I think it would matter to Morg.

1190
00:58:17,627 --> 00:58:20,755
It'd matter to all the other
guys that had gotten bagged.

1191
00:58:20,830 --> 00:58:23,424
It would matter to you,
and you know it.

1192
00:58:23,500 --> 00:58:25,263
So, you think putting
a couple of snake eyes

1193
00:58:25,335 --> 00:58:27,326
in the middle of party
headquarters is the answer?

1194
00:58:27,403 --> 00:58:28,927
Well, I don't know
if it's the answer,

1195
00:58:29,005 --> 00:58:30,267
but I'll tell you what.

1196
00:58:30,340 --> 00:58:32,205
It's going to get their
attention, isn't it?

1197
00:58:32,275 --> 00:58:35,108
You'd be going
right downtown.

1198
00:58:35,211 --> 00:58:37,475
It'd be no piece of cake.

1199
00:58:37,547 --> 00:58:39,174
Yeah, but it would be worth it.

1200
00:58:39,249 --> 00:58:42,116
And this time it's not going
to be a bunch of trees.

1201
00:58:42,185 --> 00:58:44,153
It's not going to be
a road junction.

1202
00:58:44,220 --> 00:58:46,620
It's going to be a
mission, a real mission.

1203
00:58:48,024 --> 00:58:51,050
You think it would change
anything at the peace table?

1204
00:58:53,096 --> 00:58:54,028
I don't know.

1205
00:58:54,097 --> 00:58:55,064
It might.

1206
00:58:57,133 --> 00:58:58,566
No dice.

1207
00:58:58,668 --> 00:59:00,226
I've been in this war
too long

1208
00:59:00,336 --> 00:59:02,429
to listen to this
idealistic bullshit.

1209
00:59:02,539 --> 00:59:03,301
Ah...

1210
00:59:03,373 --> 00:59:04,431
Let me tell you, friend,

1211
00:59:04,541 --> 00:59:06,634
there's nothing up there
worth dying for.

1212
00:59:06,709 --> 00:59:08,643
No, let me tell you something.

1213
00:59:08,711 --> 00:59:10,838
You risk your life.

1214
00:59:10,914 --> 00:59:13,849
You risk your life every
mission, every stinking mission.

1215
00:59:13,917 --> 00:59:15,782
I do my job.

1216
00:59:15,852 --> 00:59:19,288
I do my job.

1217
00:59:27,730 --> 00:59:29,994
Don't worry.

1218
00:59:30,066 --> 00:59:34,503
I'm going to forget
we even talked about this.

1219
00:59:39,676 --> 00:59:40,005
Dear Callie,

1220
00:59:43,012 --> 00:59:45,810
Last night, l...
I talked to my new bombardier

1221
00:59:45,882 --> 00:59:47,782
about an idea I had,

1222
00:59:47,850 --> 00:59:51,445
but he told me...
he told me it was crazy.

1223
00:59:51,554 --> 00:59:52,987
Now I'm very confused.

1224
00:59:53,056 --> 00:59:56,548
I know that I have to do
something about Morg's death,

1225
00:59:56,659 --> 00:59:58,923
but I don't know what.

1226
00:59:58,995 --> 01:00:03,295
Tonight we go out again to bomb
another useless target.

1227
01:00:03,366 --> 01:00:07,598
I miss you and little Sally.

1228
01:00:07,704 --> 01:00:08,830
I'll write again soon.

1229
01:00:08,905 --> 01:00:10,566
Jake.

1230
01:00:11,708 --> 01:00:14,609
All right, Jakey.

1231
01:00:14,677 --> 01:00:16,042
Bring it up a little tighter.

1232
01:00:18,448 --> 01:00:20,473
Here we go again.

1233
01:00:20,583 --> 01:00:22,380
Another important road junction.

1234
01:00:22,452 --> 01:00:25,717
Probably a couple of goat paths.

1235
01:00:29,225 --> 01:00:31,489
Locking down,
ground lock on target.

1236
01:00:31,561 --> 01:00:32,493
Okay.

1237
01:00:32,562 --> 01:00:34,587
Drop and try it, Jake.

1238
01:00:40,236 --> 01:00:40,930
Hack.

1239
01:00:41,004 --> 01:00:42,062
Bombs away.

1240
01:00:47,043 --> 01:00:48,806
All right, they're off.

1241
01:01:00,023 --> 01:01:01,650
Anybody see any secondaries?

1242
01:01:01,724 --> 01:01:04,750
Anybody see any secondaries?

1243
01:01:04,827 --> 01:01:07,091
I didn't think so.

1244
01:01:07,163 --> 01:01:09,131
Okay.

1245
01:01:09,198 --> 01:01:10,358
Give me some altitude.

1246
01:01:10,466 --> 01:01:11,330
Let's level off at 3,000.

1247
01:01:11,401 --> 01:01:13,130
Right with you, Boxman.

1248
01:01:18,941 --> 01:01:19,930
Oh, shit.

1249
01:01:20,009 --> 01:01:21,738
We got SAMs at 1 :00.

1250
01:01:22,945 --> 01:01:23,877
Okay, they launched.

1251
01:01:23,946 --> 01:01:24,878
Anybody see anything?

1252
01:01:24,947 --> 01:01:25,936
I think I saw two.

1253
01:01:27,950 --> 01:01:28,882
They're under that cloud bank.

1254
01:01:28,951 --> 01:01:29,781
You see it, Jake?

1255
01:01:29,852 --> 01:01:31,217
Jake!

1256
01:01:31,287 --> 01:01:32,720
Hard right! Hard right!

1257
01:01:35,224 --> 01:01:36,589
Okay, there's one left.

1258
01:01:36,659 --> 01:01:38,593
Uh, it just shut the radar down.

1259
01:01:38,661 --> 01:01:40,253
Where is the sucker? Jesus!

1260
01:01:41,097 --> 01:01:42,189
It's starting again.

1261
01:01:42,265 --> 01:01:43,994
All right, listen to me,
Box: turn into it.

1262
01:01:44,067 --> 01:01:45,557
Where? I can't see it!

1263
01:01:45,635 --> 01:01:46,693
I can't see it!

1264
01:01:50,273 --> 01:01:52,138
I'm hit, Jake, I'm hit!

1265
01:01:52,208 --> 01:01:53,607
Oh, my God, Jake!

1266
01:01:53,676 --> 01:01:54,836
Get out! Eject!

1267
01:01:54,911 --> 01:01:56,674
Punch out! Punch out!

1268
01:02:03,219 --> 01:02:04,709
He's gone.

1269
01:02:20,403 --> 01:02:22,928
Grafton.

1270
01:02:23,005 --> 01:02:26,270
Grafton...
you still with us?

1271
01:02:26,375 --> 01:02:31,335
We all miss Boxman...
but he's gone, okay?

1272
01:02:34,183 --> 01:02:35,844
Gentlemen...

1273
01:02:35,918 --> 01:02:39,183
I'd like to introduce you
to Mr. Young and Mr. Reynolds.

1274
01:02:39,255 --> 01:02:41,519
They're the replacement
crew from Hubie.

1275
01:02:41,591 --> 01:02:42,888
So why don't you go ahead

1276
01:02:42,959 --> 01:02:45,325
and tell us a little bit
about yourselves.

1277
01:02:46,629 --> 01:02:48,426
Uh... I'm Lieutenant
Larry Young.

1278
01:02:48,498 --> 01:02:50,693
Shut up, asshole.

1279
01:02:50,833 --> 01:02:52,994
Well, we've got to name them.

1280
01:02:53,102 --> 01:02:55,161
Why don't we just call 'em
"new guys."

1281
01:02:55,271 --> 01:02:57,705
We used up all the good names.

1282
01:02:57,774 --> 01:02:59,742
Let's just call them "new guys."

1283
01:02:59,876 --> 01:03:00,934
New One, New Two.

1284
01:03:01,010 --> 01:03:03,035
Very good, Razor.

1285
01:03:03,112 --> 01:03:05,376
You just have such
a vivid imagination.

1286
01:03:05,448 --> 01:03:07,746
Movie officer,
what's the film tonight?

1287
01:03:07,817 --> 01:03:09,512
There's no movie,
sir, just news.

1288
01:03:09,585 --> 01:03:12,782
Okay, news in the ready room.

1289
01:03:12,855 --> 01:03:15,517
There will be a memorial service

1290
01:03:15,591 --> 01:03:20,221
for Box and Letto
at 1 000 tomorrow.

1291
01:03:20,329 --> 01:03:23,093
Dress is tropical white, long.

1292
01:03:23,166 --> 01:03:23,325
That'll be all.

1293
01:03:26,602 --> 01:03:29,400
A Swiss camera crew
in Hanoi, North Vietnam,

1294
01:03:29,472 --> 01:03:31,599
took this footage
of a celebration of sorts,

1295
01:03:31,707 --> 01:03:35,143
commemorating the defeat
of American air pirates.

1296
01:03:35,244 --> 01:03:36,973
Here in
People's Resistance Park,

1297
01:03:37,046 --> 01:03:40,311
they've set up trophies
of their victories:

1298
01:03:40,383 --> 01:03:42,908
grim reminders of the losses

1299
01:03:42,985 --> 01:03:47,081
taken in this seven-year-old war
over the North.

1300
01:03:56,299 --> 01:03:58,267
I'll do it.

1301
01:03:58,367 --> 01:04:01,996
I'll go downtown with you.

1302
01:04:03,639 --> 01:04:06,164
But first I want you to know
something about me.

1303
01:04:09,312 --> 01:04:12,372
I had a pilot
by the name of Jim Becker.

1304
01:04:12,515 --> 01:04:14,915
He was a good man.

1305
01:04:14,984 --> 01:04:16,383
We made an agreement

1306
01:04:16,452 --> 01:04:19,717
that if we ever went down,
one of us got hurt,

1307
01:04:19,789 --> 01:04:22,053
that the other guy would go on.

1308
01:04:24,160 --> 01:04:26,993
A SAM took us out.

1309
01:04:27,063 --> 01:04:30,555
We were down on the ground
for days,

1310
01:04:30,633 --> 01:04:37,368
sneaking around, eating bugs,
living in holes that we dug.

1311
01:04:37,440 --> 01:04:40,841
On the sixth day,
Becker stepped on a mine

1312
01:04:40,910 --> 01:04:43,242
and blew half his leg off.

1313
01:04:43,312 --> 01:04:48,944
I tied it off, and
he told me to go on.

